Gulf of Maine 2021 Annual Temperature Review

An exceptional year

2021 was an exceptionally warm year for the Gulf of Maine. It had the warmest fall on record for the area, and the second warmest summer. Much of the year the region experienced what would be considered “heatwave conditions”.

Climate Patterns

To better get a sense of what kind of year 2021 was it is helpful to relate it to what we would expect from similar years. One large factor in global weather patterns is the El Niño Southern Oscillation., here is where the year fell in regards to the El nino southern oscillation.
